  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Emergency Shelter Repair and Winterization Assistance to Earthquake-Affected Communities in Nangarhar and Kunar Provinces</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">RI provides a humanitarian intervention in the provinces of Kunar ( Asdabad, Narang, Chowk &amp;amp; Norgal districts) and Nangarhar (Kama, Kuz Kunar, Goshta, and Jalalabad districts) to support communities affected by the 26 October Badakshan Earthquake. The intervention consists of two elements &#x2013; provision of shelter repair kits &amp;amp; winterization materials as a lifesaving activity. The intervention targets households; 1,600 Category A (destroyed) &amp;amp; Category B (damaged) households through the mixed modality of cash distribution &amp;amp; some in-kind contributions for those unable to access markets. Shelter kits allow those whose homes have been partially destroyed to repair them so they are fit to provide adequate shelter &amp;amp; protection for the winter. Winterization kits consisting of clothing, sleeping equipment and fuel allow category A families (&amp;amp; some Cat B families) to keep warm, improve personal dignity especially for women &amp;amp; girls, contribute the houses they are sheltering in over the winter, as well as providing them with assets in the spring.</narrative>
  </description>
